public class NimQoS
extends NimObjectSender

Snippet 

 .....
      // Get a QoS object
      // Set a timer on the object and send
      // Set a double value on the object and send
      // Set a long value on the object and send
 
      String id = null;
 
      NimQoS qos = new NimQoS("QOS_JAVA_TEST");   // Get a QoS object with a given name
 
      qos.setDefinition("group","description","unit","unitShort",true,true,false); // Define the object (optional)
      
      qos.setTarget("Disk1");
      qos.setSampleRate(30);
      qos.setSampleMax(9000);
      qos.startTimer();
      Thread.sleep(2000);
      qos.stopTimer();
      id = qos.send();
      
      Thread.sleep(3000);
 
      qos.setValue(934.38D);
      id = qos.send();
 
      qos.setValue(true);
      id = qos.send();
      
      qos.setValue(999999999999L);
      id = qos.send();
      qos.close();           // Optional polite close down of all used network resources
 
 ....
 
      // Get a QoS object
      // Set only a counter (value) on the object and send
      // No definition is set because i now that it has been sent once before
 
      NimQoS qos = new NimQoS("QOS_JAVA_TEST2");
 
      qos.setDefinition("group","description","unit","unitShort"); // Define the object (optional)
 
      qos.setTarget("Disk1");
      qos.setValue(76);
      qos.setSampleMax(9000);
      String id = qos.send();
 
 ....
 
      // Get a asynchronous QoS object 
      // Loop through a small loop 10 times with 1 second delay (set value = loop counter)
      // Close the QoS object after the loop
 
      NimQoS qos = new NimQoS("QOS_JAVA_TEST3",true);
 
      qos.setDefinition("group","description","unit","unitShort"); // Define the object (optional)
      
      qos.setTarget("Async");
      for (int i=0;i<10;i++) {
          qos.setValue(i);
          String id = qos.send();
          Thread.sleep(1000);
      }
      qos.close();           // Optional polite close down of all used network resources

Construct a synchronous QoS bound to the given ConfigurationItem and metricId.

Parameters:
ci - the parent configuration of the created qos
metricId - for example "3", "4", in "1.1:3", "2.5:4"
objectname - for example "QOS_CPU_USAGE"
Throws:
NimException

NimQoS

public NimQoS(ConfigurationItem ci,
              String metricId,
              String objectname,
              boolean async)
       throws NimException
Construct a synchronous QoS bound to the given ConfigurationItem and metricId.

Parameters:
ci - the parent configuration of the created qos
metricId - for example "3", "4", in "1.1:3", "2.5:4"
objectname - for example "QOS_CPU_USAGE"
async - true to create an "asynchronous" QoS definition (for a QoS metric that is not expected to be delivered at regular intervals.) The sample standard deviation and rate will not be sent during send()for asynchronous QoS objects that are sent.
Throws:
NimException

Return the device identifier for the device that is being monitored by this QoS measurement. The device identifier is an md5 hash that uniquely identifies the device being monitored.

Returns:
the device identifier
Throws:
NimException

getMetId

public String getMetId()
                throws NimException
Return the metric identifier for the particular metric that is being monitored by this QoS measurement. The metric identifier is an md5 hash that uniquely identifies the combination of configuration item, device, and particular measurement.

Returns:
the metric identifier
Throws:
NimException

setDevId

public void setDevId(String devId)
Set the device identifier for this QoS measurement. This method is provided for special situations in which the component sending the message is not the same component that created the original ConfigurationItem and Metric. Using the constructors with Configuration Item and metric ID are preferred, since these will also create the corresponding objects in the database.

Parameters:
devId - the device ID

Using the constructors with Configuration Item and metric ID are preferred, since these will also create the corresponding objects in the database.

Parameters:
